The paper discusses optimisation of discrete data using gradient-based methods, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of latent spaces and optimisation techniques suggests a focus on deep learning and neural networks, which are often discussed in the cs.LG and cs.NE sub-categories. The use of the MNIST dataset and image generation suggests a focus on computer vision, which is often discussed in the cs.CV sub-category. The use of the ChEMBL molecular dataset suggests a focus on computational chemistry and drug discovery, which could fall under the cs.SD sub-category. Overall, the paper could fit into several sub-categories, but cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.SD seem to be the most likely based on the content of the paper.
